<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Andean Forum Starts in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Third Andean Entrepreneurial
Forum was inaugurated here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two-day forum is organized by the Ministry of Industry,
Tourism, International Trade Negotiations and the Commission for
the Promotion of Peruvian Exports (PROMPEX).
</P>
<P>
The purpose of this meeting, attended by more than 1,000
entrepreneurs of the region, is to promote the
internationalization of the small and medium companies that cannot
export their products or that have little experience in this
activity.
</P>
<P>
It is also sought to establish trade contacts between the
businessmen of Peru, Ecuador, Bolivia, Colombia, Venezuela,
Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay, Paraguay and Chile, said PROMPEX
General Manager Antonio Castillo.
</P>
<P>
The Minister of Industry Juan Hurtado, who also is the chairman
of the Andean Community Commission, said that its members are
aware that their right is to face and consolidate the economy of
the region with efficiency, as well as to reduce the costs to be
more competitive and offer better advantages.
</P>
<P>
Andean Community General Secretary Sebastian Alegrett said that
this year expectations are centered on the growth of the economy
in the region, foreseen to be 2.3 percent of the gross domestic
product (GDP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
