<HEADLINE> French Communist Party Opens 30th Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The French Communist Party (PCF)
opened its 30th national congress on Thursday in Martigues near
Marseilles with a theme focused on helping push forward social
reforms in France.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Paul Magnon, member of the leading secretariat of the
party, said in his opening speech that the objective of the
political action of PCF is ``the construction of the dynamic for
changes.''
</P>
<P>
``We want to contribute to transform the expectations of
millions of citizens into social movement which can impose
structural reforms,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 900 representatives of 200,000 PCF members are attending
the four-day congress, which was opened with a song paying homage
to some Communist resistance fighters who were executed by Nazis
in 1943.
</P>
<P>
The National Secretary of PCF, Robert Hue, the Minister of
Transport Jean-Claude Gayssot and hundreds of PCF delegates
traveled to Martigues from Paris on a special bullet train
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
