<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Flood Death Toll Rises to 640 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from the
devastating flood in southern and central Mozambique since early
February has risen to 640, and 95 others are still missing, a
government spokesman said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Macheve, spokesman of the National Disaster Management
Institute, said that 380 people died in the southern province of
Gaza alone, where most of the deaths occurred in the beleaguered
district of Chokwe, with 200 people dead in massive flooding on
the Limpopo River.
</P>
<P>
He said the death toll is expected to rise but renewed flooding
is now hindering search attempt.
</P>
<P>
Some two million people were affected by the flood and half a
million of them were left homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
