<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over Half of Men Over 40 Affected by Impotence: Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Impotence affected over half
of men aged 40 and over, a leading South African expert on the
subject said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Darryl Sleep, a professor of Urology at Pretoria University and
Pretoria Academic Hospital, said international studies had shown
that 52 percent of men aged 40 and over experienced mild, moderate
or severe erectile dysfunction, as he was addressing the 22nd
Biennial Congress of the Urological Association of South Africa in
Durban. .
</P>
<P>
Complete erectile dysfunction occurred in five percent of those
aged 40 and older, he was quoted by South African Press
Association as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the impotence problem was a great deal worse than
previously thought, adding he was surprised that studies done in
both developed and developing countries showed similar results.
</P>
<P>
The congress was attended by several world medical authorities
from the United States, Britain, Ireland, Australia, Canada and
other African countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
