<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Arrests 27 Illegal Aliens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven illegal foreign
immigrants were arrested in northern Zambia on Thursday, an
immigration officer said.
</P>
<P>
Immigration department public relations officer Denny Lungu
said here that they were arrested in an early morning operation in
Kitwe and would appear in court soon.
</P>
<P>
Lungu could not give the origin of these illegal immigrants.
</P>
<P>
Lungu said that the department arrested 164 illegal immigrants
of various nationalities last month.
</P>
<P>
The officer warned that the department would continue to deal
ruthlessly with anyone flouting immigration laws of the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
