<HEADLINE> Yemeni President to Visit Canada, U.S., Italy, Vatican </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
will start a state visit to Canada, the United States, Italy and
the Vatican on March 25.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in the U.S., Saleh will meet U.S. President Bill
Clinton and Secretary of State Madeleine Albright as well as other
senior officials and congressmen on bilateral ties and partnership
between Yemen and the U.S. in various areas.
</P>
<P>
In Canada, Italy and the Vatican, he will discuss with their
leaders ways of boosting cooperation and other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Saleh's tour of Canada and the United States is the first by a
Yemeni head of state since 1989.
</P>
<P>
"The Yemeni-U.S. ties are good and grow steadily," the Arabic
daily Al-Hayat on Thursday quoted Saleh as saying.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that his tour would open new horizons for the
development of the Yemeni-U.S. ties.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Canada and Italy are all significant
investors in Yemen's oil, gas and metals sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
