<HEADLINE> Consensus on EU Growth Objectives: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A consensus was being reached
Thursday among the European Union leaders as regards the
transformation of the 15-nation bloc into a more competitive
economy.
</P>
<P>
Maria Joao Rodrigues, advisor to Portuguese Prime Minister
Antonio Guterres, said that the 15 EU member states agreed during
their first-day session to develop ambitious policies for the
information society, to carry out economic reforms, to go ahead
with the renovation of the European social model and to promote
macro-economic measures that ensure sustained development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on behalf of Portugal that is holding the rotating EU
presidency, Rodrigues told the press that the 15 EU member states
were also reaching consensus on the methods needed to reach the
objective of transforming EU into an economy that can compete with
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The EU leaders, with prime ministers, foreign and finance
ministers plus two presidents, decided to set a deadline for the
approval of a package of measures on European telecommunications
and to indicate a time limit for the approval of guidelines on e-
commerce.
</P>
<P>
Time limits will also be set for other objectives such as the
connection of European schools to the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Summit participants agreed to create a high debit network along
with a trans-European communications network to lunge the EU into
the world's most competitive economic turf within the next decade.
</P>
