<HEADLINE> More Arrests Follow Assassination Attempt on Karabakh Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Police in Nagorno-Karabakh
Thursday arrested "numerous people" suspected of involvement in an
assassination attempt Wednesday on President Arkady Gukasian of
the self-proclaimed republic inside Azerbaijan, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The arrests came after Wednesday's detention of former Karabakh
Defense Minister Samvel Babaian and some of his supporters shortly
after Gukasian, his driver and bodyguard were wounded in a
shooting in Stepanokert.
</P>
<P>
Babaian was dismissed last December due to a stand-off with the
Gukasian-led government, which accused Babaian of "defending
personal and clan interests, of resorting to all manner of methods
including provocation aimed at derailing the president's course
and demanding his resignation."
</P>
<P>
Nagorno-Karabakh is an ethnic Armenia enclave inside Azerbaijan.
Yerevan and Baku have been at odds over the status of Karabakh.
</P>
<P>
Arms and ammunition have been found in the homes of some of the
28 people detained earlier, Interfax said, quoting an official of
Karabakh's Prosecutor's Office.
</P>
<P>
Gukasian, his driver and bodyguards have been whisked to
Yerevan, the Armenian capital, for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The Prosecutor's Office said three bullets went through
Gukasian's leg, the driver suffered wounds to the head, kidney and
lungs, and the bodyguard was shot in the spine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
