economic changes that called for food management by other sectors
other than governments.
</P>
<P>
The training would focus on national and regional centers that
deal with food security, he said.
</P>
<P>
Food security in the SADC region is being threatened by
torrential rains induced by cyclone Eline that devastated parts of
Mozambique, South Africa, Zambia, Botswana, Swaziland and
Zimbabwe in February.
</P>
<P>
The torrential rains caused massive loss of crops and
threatened yields in affected areas. 
