<HEADLINE> ACP-EU Parliamentary Assembly Ends in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
By Song Li
</P>
<P>
ABUJA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Parliamentarians from African,
Caribbean, Pacific (ACP) and their European Union (EU)
counterparts Thursday ended their four-day meeting in Nigeria's
capital Abuja with a resolve to intensify their partnership
cooperation under new agreements to be signed in Fiji in June.
</P>
<P>
At the closing of the 30th ACP-EU Parliamentary Assembly, the
ACP co- president Louis Clair said the new accords to replace the
25-year-old Lome I-IV convention that expired last month, would
elevate the age-long North- South cooperation to "new ways of
doing things" in the future.
</P>
<P>
The new agreement to be signed in Suva the Fijian capital on
June 4 would emphasize democracy, human rights and good governance
in the appropriation of the European development fund, on which
development projects are financed in ACP countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 45 billion U.S. dollars has been put into ACP countries
since 1975, but it seemed not to have benefited the people. That
is why there must be an emphasis shift, according to Clair.
</P>
<P>
"We are in support of efforts to alleviate poverty in
developing nations, especially, the 39 highest indebted countries,
but we cannot do it alone, this must be done in partnership," he
added.
</P>
<P>
With the trend on globalization and free trade, the
co-president said the ACP countries should try and promote trade
among themselves well beyond the current neglectable level.
</P>
<P>
He said enlargement of the European Union would bring new
opportunities to the ACP countries as the market for ACP products
would also be enlarged.
</P>
<P>
Some 600 parliamentarians attended the assembly, which is the
largest international meeting hosted by Nigeria's civilian
government since it took over from the military last May.
</P>
<P>
In addition to delegates from the 86 ACP and EU member
countries, the Organization of African Unity, African Development
Bank, and other inter- governmental organizations also sent their
representatives to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The 31st assembly takes places at the ACP-EU headquarters in
Brussels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
