who are suffering from TB are HIV positive."
</P>
<P>
The only way to reduce TB cases was to treat everyone that was
 suffering from the disease because it could be easily infect the
next person as it was an airborne disease.
</P>
<P>
However, it was disappointing to note that most TB patients did
not finish their treatment courses, she said.
</P>
<P>
"Most patients stop taking drugs after feeling better, but as
an association we are working on monitoring them as of now, we
have trained people who make follow-ups to make sure that
patients stick to their drugs,"
</P>
<P>
she said. 
