<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A meeting to mark the World Water
Day (March 22) and the World Meteorology Day (March 23) was held
here on Thursday by Vietnam's General Department of Meteorology
and Hydrology (GDMH), Vietnam News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, GDMH General Director Nguyen Cong Thanh
spoke highly of Vietnam's hydro-meteorology service's
contributions to minimizing the consequences of natural disasters
by keeping the community informed of weather patterns.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting, Vietnam's Deputy Prime Minister Pham
Gia Khiem stressed that global climate and environmental changes
have seriously affected water resources - a vital factor for life
and planetary development.
</P>
