<HEADLINE> France Seeks Chair of European Reconstruction, Development Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 23 (Xinhua) -- France is seeking the presidency of
the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) as its
president Horst Koehler is leaving his post for the International
Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
Officials of the French Ministry of Economy and Finance, quoted
by the French economic daily "Tribune," said Thursday that Jean
Lemiere, director of the French Treasury, would be an excellent
candidate for the EBRD leadership because of his experiences in
financial affairs.
</P>
<P>
French government sources said that France is interested in
this post because France is an important contributor to the
multilateral financing projects for Eastern European countries.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD was established to contribute to the construction of
market economy in Eastern Europe after the fall of the Berlin Wall.
</P>
<P>
Lemiere is also the president of the European Economic and
Financial Committee, an informal organ in charge of preparing for
the meetings of finance ministers of the European Union countries
and the Council of Europe. 
</P>
