<HEADLINE> Russia, U.S. to Intensify Cooperation in United Nations (Updated with more quotes) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia and the United
States both said Thursday that they agree to strengthen their
cooperation in the United Nations in order make the world body "
more efficient and more responsive to the challenges of the new
millennium."
</P>
<P>
The was jointly announced by Sergey Lavrov, Russian permanent
representative to the United Nations, and Richard Holbrooke, U.S.
permanent representative to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
"The Russian Federation and the United States agree to
intensify Russian-American cooperation in the United Nations in
order to promote broad agreement on practical ways and means to
support the reform process with the aim of making the United
Nations more efficient and more responsive to the challenges of
the new millennium," a brief joint statement, read by Lavrov to
the press here, said.
</P>
<P>
"The Russian Federation and the United States share an
obligation to encourage the United Nations to the greatest
possible effectiveness and efficiency, especially in maintaining
and enhancing international peace and security in accordance with
the U.N. Charter," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"Our ministers asked their ambassadors in New York and their
respective ministries to work together with others toward this end,
" the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Russia and the United States are two of the five permanent
members with veto power on the 15-nation U.N. Security Council,
which, under the U.N. Charter, has the primary responsibility for
the maintenance of peace and security in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
