<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets British Parliamentarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, here today told Ben
Chapman, chairman of the Britain-China Group of British parliament,
and other parliamentarians from the group that the frequent
exchanges between the two legislative bodies can further promote
bilateral state-to-state relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that Britain was among the first Western countries to
forge diplomatic ties with new China. After the return of Hong
Kong to the motherland, Sino-British relations entered a new era,
he pointed out, adding that high-level exchanges between the two
countries in recent years have promoted friendly cooperation in
all fields.
</P>
<P>
Inter-parliamentary exchanges constitute an important part of
inter-state relations, he said. The NPC and the British parliament
have enhanced their exchanges in recent years and both have played
an important role in their respective political and social lives,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The NPC and the British parliament should further their
contacts and cooperation so as to promote the relations between
the two countries in other fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that members from the group could get to
know China's reality through the visit and continue to play their
part as a bridge between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li also exchanged views with the guests on a number of issues.
</P>
<P>
Chapman said that the Britain-China Group, now with more than
150 members, is the largest group in the British parliament,
demonstrating the interest of British legislators in getting to
know more about China, a country which has scored rapid growth and
undergone changes. The best way to follow such changes, Chapman
noted, is to visit the country personally. He told Li the group is
ready to further their efforts to enhance mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
Chapman and his group are here as guest of the NPC's China-
Britain Friendship Group.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, was
among those present at the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
