<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Seized Large Amount of Drugs Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, March 23 (Xinhua) -- China's border defense
departments seized 17 tons of heroin, ice and hemp in 1,200 drug
trafficking cases last year, arresting 1,933 suspects, a national
meeting revealed today.
</P>
<P>
The border defense department of southwest China cracked 669
drug cases, eight of which involved more than 10 kilograms of
drugs each, according to a national meeting on fighting narcotics
trafficking, which closed here today.
</P>
<P>
In the coastal areas of southeast China, drug traffickers often
use international freighters to transport drugs. In 1999, coastal
departments of border defense and public security seized 527
kilograms of "ice".
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the meeting showed that the number of
registered drug users in China had increased to 680,000 last year,
up 14.3 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1999, there were more than 17,000 HIV/AIDS
patients in 31 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities,
and 72 percent of them caught the disease through drug injections.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Biggest Green Battery Production Center Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 23 (Xinhua) -- China's biggest environmentally-
friendly battery production center was set up today in Mianyang
City, Sichuan Province, in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The center, known as the Changhong Battery Industrial Park, is
capable of producing about 300 million pieces of environmentally-
friendly batteries, valued at over 500 million yuan (about 60.9
million US dollars) with four production lines imported from
Japanese electronics giant Toshiba.
</P>
<P>
The investment in the initial stage of development of the
center totaled 300 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The park specializes in the development and production of
alkaline storage batteries, and is the largest agglomeration-type
battery center in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The major investor is China's biggest television producer,
Changhong Electronic Group Co. Ltd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
