<HEADLINE> 24-hour Internet Cafe Opens in Subic Freeport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A first-of-its-kind 24-hour
internet cafe recently opened in Subic Freeport in the northern
Philippines servicing students, businessmen, mall hoppers,
Philippine News Agency (PNA said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cafe is just one of the new facilities at a mall in the
country's Freeport, the PNA said, adding that the cafe boasts of
state-of-the-art computer and communications equipment allowing
easier and faster access to the world-wide web.
</P>
<P>
Equipped with 35 personal computers, high-tech modems and a hip
environment that allows one to surf the internet, the cafe is the
first to offer its services on a round-the-clock basis.
</P>
<P>
The cafe also aims to help make the Freeport a software
development and maintenance area and to introduce people with the
advantage of e-commerce, the PNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
