<HEADLINE> SENSEX Declines on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (SENSEX)
declined in share values Thursday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (
BSE) due to operators squared-up their outstanding position in the
absence of follow-up buying support.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share sensitive index closed at 5,115.02 as against
Wednesday's close of 5,201.87, netting a loss of 86.85 points or 1.
67 percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index, however, moved up marginally by 10.33 points
to 2,920.77 from previous close of 2,910.44.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were more or less steady at
630.50 and 240.76 from their previous close of 629.54 and 240.51
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index edged up by 1.42 points to 1,919.75 from
Wednesday's close of 1,918.33. 
</P>
</TEXT>
