<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Musharraf Puts Economic Revival, Good Governance as  Top Priorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Chief Executive
General Pervez Musharraf Thursday said that revival of economy and
good governance are top priorities of his government.
</P>
<P>
Replying to a question at his press conference here, Musharraf
pointed out that there were three main problems in the economy,
that is, debt burden, budget deficit and trade deficit.
</P>
<P>
He said a comprehensive plan has been chalked out to accelerate
privatization process and 90 percent of the privatization proceeds
will be used for debt retirement, while the rest will be allocated
for poverty alleviation.
</P>
<P>
Musharraf said budgetary deficit will be curtailed by two
billion rupees (38 million U.S. dollars) for the current fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive also said that the export target of over
nine billion dollars will be achieved, registering an increase of
20 percent over last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
