<HEADLINE> Indonesian Attorney General's Office to Summon  Soeharto Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian former President
Soeharto will soon be summoned for questioning in connection with
alleged corruption during his three-decade rule, Attorney General
Marzuki Darusman told reporters here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Marzuki said his office would serve a new summons on Soeharto
next week.
</P>
<P>
The 78-year-old former ruler was named as a suspect for alleged
corruption during his rule after Marzuki decided to reopen the
case in December last year.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Attorney General's Office summoned Soeharto for the
same purpose but the latter did not show up on the ground that he
was not in good health.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto was declared medically fit after undergoing two
examinations last week by a team of doctors at state-owned Cipto
Manungkusumo General Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
