<HEADLINE> Gold, Silver Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Gold prices reacted down
sharply on the bullion market Thursday in Mumbai (Bombay) in line
with weak Hong Kong advices, while silver also remained subdued on
poor demand.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold declined further to close at 4,545 rupees (105.70
U.S. dollars) per 10 grams, showing a fresh fall of 35 rupees (0.
81 dollar) over the previous day's close of 4,580 rupees (106.51
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two-carat gold was nominally quoted weak at 4,205 rupees
(97.79 dollars) per 10 grams from the last level of 4,235 rupees (
98.49 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (.999 fineness) closed at 8,010 rupees
(186.28 dollars) per kilogram, showing a fall of 20 rupees (0.46
dollar) over the last close of 8,030 rupees (186.74 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) dropped by 15 rupees (0.35 dollar)
to 7,885 rupees (183.37 dollars) per kg. from 7,900 rupees (183.72
dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
