<HEADLINE> Russia's Unity Movement Officially Registered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Unity party, which threw
its weight behind Acting President Vladimir Putin, was officially
registered as a nationwide political movement on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Russian Justice Minister Yuri Chaika Thursday gave Deputy
Prime Minister Sergei Shoigu, leader of the movement, a
certificate for the registration, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The Unity party, which was established only two months before
the parliamentary elections in December, did extremely well in the
elections and won 81 seats in the State Duma or lower house of
parliament, only second to the Communist Party with 94 seats.
</P>
<P>
Chaika described the registration as a major event in Russia's
political life.
</P>
<P>
Shoigu said the youth organization of the movement will hold a
convention in April while the second stage of Unity's congress is
scheduled for May 20 when the formation of a party is to be
announced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
