<HEADLINE> Ullrich Out of Criterium International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Former Tour de France winner Jan
Ullrich has withdrew from this weekend's Criterium International
in France, reports said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The German rider also missed the Milan-San Remo classic last
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"At the moment I need to compete in long events rather than
short, fast races," said Ullrich, who resumed training on
Wednesday after fighting a stomach bug.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich won the Tour in 1997 and came second to Italian Marco
Pantani in 1998. He missed last year's race due to injury.
</P>
