<HEADLINE> 30 Palestinian Prisoners Return to Gaza, West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven Palestinian prisoners,
released by Israel in a gesture of "goodwill" on the occasion of
Eid al-Adha, the Muslim Feast of Sacrifice, arrived Thursday
afternoon to Gaza strip.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, three others arrived in the West Bank town of
Tulkurm, according to Palestinian resources.
</P>
<P>
This batch of Palestinian prisoners were convicted of criminal
charges and the Israeli government decided to free them with other
16 prisoners convicted of "security crimes."
</P>
<P>
Since signing Sharm el Sheikh memorandum with the Palestinian
side, Israel has released 429 Palestinian prisoners, most of them
are either political prisoners or so-called security threat.
</P>
<P>
There are still more than 1,500 Palestinian prisoners detained
in the Israeli jails. 
</P>
</TEXT>
