<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Musharraf Announces Local Election Framework in  Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Chief Executive
General Pervez Musharraf Thursday announced to hold local body
polls in December this year, while refusing to give any timeframe
for national and provincial elections.
</P>
<P>
"I have not yet thought about the holding of national and
provincial assemblies elections. These elections will be held
after the process of local bodies is completed," Musharraf said
while spelling out "a framework for devolution of power and
responsibility at the grass-roots levels" here.
</P>
<P>
According to Musharraf, union council elections at the village
level will be held from December this year to May, 2001 and
district-level elections will begin in July, 2001.
</P>
<P>
Following the local polls, elections for provincial assemblies
will be held and the National Assembly and Senate polls will be
ensuing, the general said.
</P>
<P>
General Musharraf, who assumed the post of chief executive of
Pakistan after a bloodless coup in October last year, and his
government have long been under enormous pressure from inside and
outside to "return to democracy", that is, to hold the general
elections.
</P>
<P>
This issue is expected to be high on U.S. President Bill
Clinton's agenda when he visits Pakistan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Spelling out the outline of the district and local government
plan, Musharraf said it will consist of three tiers namely
district councils, sub-district councils and union councils.
</P>
<P>
District and union council members will be elected through
direct elections and sub-district council members and members of
union councils through indirect elections.
</P>
<P>
Musharraf said that the plan will realize the empowerment of
women by giving equal representations in all levels of bodies.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive also announced lowering the voters' age by
three years, from the present 21 years to 18 years, to broaden
voting base and ensure maximum participation of the youth.
</P>
<P>
These elections, he said, will be held on a non-party basis.
</P>
<P>
Musharraf described local elections he envisaged as "a peaceful,
constructive, democratic, dynamic revolution whose sole objective
is to place in hands of the people the power to shape their own
destiny."
</P>
<P>
"The people themselves will become empowered to take charge of
the foundations of democracy and of the system by which they are
governed," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
