<HEADLINE> Jinan to Renovate Old Urban Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The capital city of coastal
Shandong Province in east China will invest 25 billion yuan to
renovate its old urban areas over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
A total of 3.4 million square meters of rundown houses will be
demolished, and nearly eight million square meters of new housing
will be put up.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will also be made to develop stores, tourist and
recreational facilities, and public facilities in the city.
</P>
<P>
This will provide good opportunities for real estate developers.
Statistics show that the city now has only 38 real estate
development companies, which is hardly enough to cater to the
demand of a renewed urban landscape.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities said that all large real estate projects will
be carried out through bidding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
