<HEADLINE> Shanghai Improves Meteorological Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The meteorological service in
this east China metropolis has not only helped prevent and fight
against disasters in the past few years, it has also provided
reference for major decisions on construction and public services,
according to an activity held here today to mark World
Meteorological Day.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai meteorological departments have made prompt
forecasts of typhoons, which frequently hit the city, and helped
the city avoid severe economic losses.
</P>
<P>
The major construction projects in the city have also benefited
from the weather forecasts, which have guaranteed safe weather
conditions for high-altitude construction work.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the meteorological service for agriculture, the
city has also opened weather information hotlines and other kinds
of public weather services. In addition, he meteorological
departments cooperate with the municipal environment protection
bureau to provide air quality forecasts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
