<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Host Int'l Children's Art Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The China Welfare Institute is
to host the Third International Children's Art Festival during
July 28 to August 2 in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Founded in Hong Kong on June 14, 1938 by Soong Ching Ling, the
institution works for the development of China's women and
children.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ping, vice-president of the institute, said that the
institution successfully held the first art festival in 1993. An
African girl became the first invited guest after finding a bottle
drifting in the sea containing a message from the  organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
Children from 27 countries and regions gathered in Shanghai to
attend the second festival in 1997. Ten of them received their
invitations by means of pigeons carrying messages from the
organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
This year's guests will be selected through contests on the
Internet, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Children's art troupes from 20 countries and regions, including
the United States, Japan, Australia and Austria, have registered
for the festival so far. 
</P>
