<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Three Major Millennium Events in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region will organize three major events in
May as part of the millennium celebrations.
</P>
<P>
They are the "Coming of Age" ceremony, French Riding
Performance and the Chi Lin Nunnery Opening Ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Announcing details of the Dragon Year 2000 celebration program
Thursday, Secretary for Home Affairs David Lan said "to tie in
with the Dragon's Spirit which symbolizes hope, energy, resilience
and confidence, these events are designed to enhance community and
international harmony, as well as racial and cultural integration.
Their ultimate objective is to promote social harmony and
community solidarity."
</P>
<P>
"Through these events, we also hope to project Hong Kong's
image as a prosperous cosmopolitan city," Lan added.
</P>
<P>
The "Coming of Age" ceremony will be held on May 4 in the Grand
Hall of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center with a
gathering of thousands of youngsters who reach 18 this year.
</P>
<P>
The French National Riding Academy will give a unique horse
opera performed in balletic movements to classical music from May
12 to 14 in the Hong Kong Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
Its 27 horses with riders in full regalia will be accompanied
by the Hong Kong Philharmonic Orchestra and the soprano opera
singer Lucille Vignon.
</P>
<P>
The Chi Lin Nunnery, an ingenious merging of ancient
architecture with modern technology, will be opened on May 18.
</P>
<P>
"The magnificent and intricate design of the nunnery will
certainly impress local and overseas visitors alike, regardless of
their religious affiliation," Lan said.
</P>
<P>
Other programs in the coming months will include the Children
Reading Pledge, International/Asian Harmony Extravaganza, 100
Years of Hong Kong Fashion Exhibition, FIBA Diamond Ball Hong Kong
2000, and the Euro Christmas Carnival. 
</P>
