<HEADLINE> Beijing's Foreign Trade Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital imported and
exported 1.29 billion US dollars worth of goods in the first two
months this year, up 39 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the city's exports stood at 504
million US dollars in the two-month period, up 43.1 percent, while
imports reached 786 million US dollars, up 36.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Imports and exports of general trade and machinery and
electronic products increased sharply in the two-month period,
local sources said.
</P>
<P>
Imports of overseas-funded enterprises increased 47.7 percent,
and their exports surpassed that of state-owned enterprises for
the first time.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that Beijing's exports to Japan, the United States,
and the European Union grew at a double-digit rate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
