<HEADLINE> World Bank Funds Road Construction in Shanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has provided more
than 57 million yuan in loans to Yuncheng Prefecture in north
China's Shanxi Province to build roads over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
With these loans, Yuncheng has built six highways with a
combined length of 204 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The highways, all in remote poor areas, have benefited 250,000
people, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
Luliang Prefecture, another poor area in the province, also
received World Bank loans to build five highways.
</P>
<P>
Authorities note that these roads have greatly improved the
investment environment of Shanxi province.  
</P>
