<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia's Foreign Trade Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region in North China saw its foreign trade volume surge by 60
percent to 248 million US dollars-worth in the first two months of
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the region's Foreign Economic Relations and Trade
department, Inner Mongolia exported 149 million US dollars-worth
of goods in the January-February period, up 40 percent on an
annual basis, while its imports doubled to 71.47 million US
dollars-worth.
</P>
<P>
With the recovery of the Asian economy, Inner Mongolia's
exports to the Republic of Korea and Southeast Asia rose by 33-
and 29-fold, respectively, in the two months.
</P>
<P>
During the two months, Inner Mongolia approved the
establishment of ten foreign-invested companies, and signed 16
contracts involving overseas construction projects abroad and
labor export. 
</P>
