<HEADLINE> China's First Peking Opera Graduates to Perform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- China's first group of 26
graduate students majoring in Peking Opera performance will make
their debut tomorrow at Beijing's Chang'an Theater.
</P>
<P>
They will perform there from March 24 to 30, the Beijing Youth
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
During their three-year campus life at Chinese Opera Institute,
these actors were trained theoretically and practically, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
While studying at the institute, the 26 opera singers also
joined their colleagues to perform eight months a year.
</P>
<P>
Their mentors said the graduates' artistic level was greatly
raised after their graduate school education, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Peking Opera had long pursued the tradition of one-to-one
teaching, which limited the number of skilled trainees.
</P>
<P>
The institute plans to train more graduates of performers in
Peking Opera in the coming years, the newspaper said. 
</P>
