<HEADLINE> Turkey Reaffirms Its "One China Policy" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 22 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Foreign Ministry said
Wednesday that Turkey will adhere to its "One China Policy".
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministry made clear its position toward China
following local elections in Taiwan province of China.
</P>
<P>
Turkey will continue to develop its relations with China and
not have any political relations with Taiwan, the Foreign Ministry
stated in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry stressed that Turkey only has economic,
trade and cultural contacts with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Turkey evaluates the elections held in Taiwan on March 18
within the framework of the principle of "One China Policy", the
Foreign Ministry emphasized.
</P>
<P>
It said Turkey wishes that peace will dominate relations across
the Taiwan Straits, adding he hoped that the results of the
elections will contribute to the re-unification of China through
peaceful negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has attached importance to expanding its relations with
China in all fields. At the last End-of-Year Press Conference,
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel said that "we are determined to
develop our relations with China in all areas and to further our
cooperation in order to benefit from the opportunities presented
by the global economy."
</P>
<P>
Demirel said that "with its enormous human and economic
resources, its deep historical roots, and its great potential for
development, China will be one of the most important global actors
of the 21st Century." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
