<HEADLINE> Johnson Eyes World 300m Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Double Olympic champion
Michael Johnson hopes to add a rarely 300 meters world record to
his 200 and 400 world marks in South Africa's premier athletics
meeting in Pretoria on Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old maitained a superb form after clocking the
fourth fastest time ever over the 200 last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
American Danny Everett and Cuban Roberto Hernandez jointly set
the present world 300 mark of 31.48 seconds a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
Czech javelin world record holder Jan Zelezny and veteran
German Juergen Schult, the world shot put record holder, will also
appear in the grand prix II event. 
</P>
