<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua)-- The Republic of Korea (ROK) will
further increase its cooperation with China in the field of high
and new technologies, according to Kwon Byong-hyon, the ROK's
ambassador to China.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, he said that the ROK wishes to
expand the exchange of scientists and scholars and increase
spending for scientific and technological contact between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
There will be a bright future for hi-tech cooperation between
the two countries, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in recent years, the two sides have conducted a
series of fruitful exchanges in various fields, such as
telecommunications, information know-how, the automotive industry,
high definition television and aerospace.
</P>
<P>
China and the ROK hold a ministerial-level meeting every two
years to discuss programs of cooperation, Kwon Byong-hyon said on
the sidelines of a seminar on ROK-China cooperation in high and
new technologies.
</P>
<P>
He said China enjoys advantages in the basic sciences and other
areas, and the ROK has advantages in applied and commercial
technologies.
</P>
<P>
If the two countries can combine their respective advantages,
this will be mutually beneficial to both, he concluded.  
</P>
