<HEADLINE> China Selects Annual Top-Ten Relics Exhibitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- China's State Administration of
Cultural Heritage today selected an exhibition highlighting the
ancient tombs of Mancheng in north Hebei Province as one of the 10
best sites of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The awards list also includes exhibitions of art at the Nanjing
Museum, the Eternal Civilization show of the Luoyang Museum, Henan
Province, the cliff pictures of the Baotou Museum in Inner
Mongolia, the ancient ruins at the Sichuan Museum, Tibetan history
and culture at the Tibet Museum, Sun Yat-sen's life account at the
Sun Yat-sen Memorial Hall in Guangdong Province, the packaging art
of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) at the Palace Museum, the ancient
culture show at the Jingzhou Museum in Hubei Province, and the
show on the history and culture of the Western Xia Dynasty (1038-
1227) in the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Five other museums including the Zhengzhou Museum in Henan, the
Weifang Museum in Shandong, the Hefei Museum in Anhui, the Capital
Museum in Beijing, and the Heilongjiang Museum were also nominated.
</P>
<P>
The annual selection of the top-10 exhibitions began in 1997 as
part of an effort to encourage museums to exhibit high-quality
works of art.
</P>
<P>
Every year, about 90 million people visit over 7,000
exhibitions at 1,300 museums in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
