<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Shows Downturn Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Frayed nerves and cash shortage
hammered stocks here Wednesday by 3.8 percent, pushing the downturn
to the hilt as more investors made a hasty exit, the Cypurs Mail
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Investors continued to sell in a broad-based decline which has
to date brought the all-share Cyprus Stock Exchange (CSE) index
tumbling 32 percent since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday brought another sharp decline. The all-share index
shot down to 483.69 points, 19 points lower than Tuesday's close,
and straying clear of the 500-point mark, seen as a tentative
support level by some.
</P>
<P>
Traded value stood steady at 17.4 million Cyprus pounds (29.5
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Retail and commercial stocks fared the worst, falling between
six and five percent. Banking stocks, which had underperformed the
market losses recently, were also affected.
</P>
<P>
The banking index lost 2.9 percent. Bank of Cyprus hit a new low
for this year when it lost 26 cents, closing at 7.90 pounds (13.40
dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
