<HEADLINE> Singapore to Host APEC Education Ministerial Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Second APEC Education Ministerial Meeting (AEMM) is
expected to be attended by some 150 ministers and senior officials
of the 21 APEC economies, the Singapore Ministry of Education (MOE)
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The main theme for the meeting is "Education for Learning
Societies in the 21st Century," according to the MOE.
</P>
<P>
The AEMM serves as a forum to discuss common education issues
and identify strategies for addressing challenges to education
systems, within the broader economic, social and cultural
environment of the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The first AEMM was held in Washington D.C. in 1992 and the APEC
leaders decided in 1997 to hold the second AEMM in Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The MOE said the APEC decision to hold the second AEMM reflects
the recognition of the increasing importance of education in the
development of economies.
</P>
<P>
As part of the second AEMM, the MOE is also organizing the
Learning Metropolis Exhibition and the Education 2000 Conference.
</P>
