<HEADLINE> Obuchi Welcomes Agreement to Resume Tokyo, Pyongyang Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo
Obuchi on Thursday welcomed an agreement between Japan and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) to hold their first
round of negotiations on normalizing diplomatic ties on April 4-8.
</P>
<P>
"I am delighted" that the normalization talks with the DPRK are
going to be resumed after a long period of discontinuation, Obuchi
told reporters at his official residence in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese prime minister expressed the hope that concrete
results will be achieved toward solving bilateral issues in the
talks.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Foreign Minister Yohei Kono on Wednesday announced
that Japan and the DPRK have agreed on the timetable for the talks.
</P>
<P>
The talks, which are to be held in Pyongyang, will mark the
resumption of normalization negotiations which have been suspended
for nearly eight years.
</P>
<P>
The previous talks between the two countries on normalizing
ties began in January 1991, but collapsed after eight rounds in
November 1992. 
</P>
