<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Has Consistent Policy on Kosovo Issue (2)  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S.-led NATO's action "seriously violated the UN charter
and the norms of the international law, and set a dangerous
precedent for intervention into other country's internal affairs
by military force," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo situation remains tense, with increased ethnic
strife and conflict, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the situation in the past year provided the
entire world two profound warnings. First, the new interventionism,
which puts human rights above sovereignty, can't solve the so-
called human rights issue. Instead, it will further complicate the
already- existing dispute, and cause disastrous results, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
Second, such principles of the UN Charter as equality of
sovereignty and non-interference in other country's internal
affairs are far from outdated, he said. On the contrary, these
principles still have great practical significance.
</P>
<P>
Sun said China hopes that U.S.-led NATO will reflect deeply on
and draw lessons from what has happened in Kosovo in order to
avoid creating any situation which goes against the wishes of the
people of the world for peace and development at the turn of the
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
