<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Has Consistent Policy on Kosovo Issue (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi made these remarks
at a press conference here this afternoon when asked about China's
view of the 78-day bombing of Yugoslavia by U.S.-led NATO nearly a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
"By so doing, conditions necessary for a political solution of
the Kosovo issue can be created," he said, adding that China has
no self-interest in this matter, but has taken a principled stance
aimed at safeguarding the UN Charter and the widely recognized
norms governing international relations.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that U.S.-led NATO took military action against
Yugoslavia, a sovereign state, using the issue of Kosovo as an
excuse last year.
</P>
