<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Laos have signed an
education cooperation protocol for the year of 2000 and an
agreement on building a dormitory for foreign students at Lao
National University in Vientiane.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocol, which was signed here by Vietnamese
Minister of Education and Training Nguyen Minh Hien and visiting
Lao Minister of Education Phimmasone Leuangkhamma on Wednesday,
the education ministries of the two countries will continue
promoting cooperation in training with short-term courses,
according to reports of local press Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam will send its experts to help Laos compile school
textbooks and manage boarding schools for ethnic minority pupils
and students.
</P>
<P>
The two ministries will exchange their delegations with the aim
of investigating the fostering of teachers, regular education and
enrollment work.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Vietnam received 120 Lao students, bringing the total
number of Lao students learning in Vietnam to 457 including 33
postgraduates. 
