<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Three wealthy Italians have been
arrested by Kenyan police during their investigation of the
cold-blooded killing of another Italian in his Malindi beach
apartment in Coast Province, southeast Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Lorenzo Guisseppe Calzavacca, 76, was found in a pool of blood
with his hands and legs bound with ropes at the Oasis Village
apartment complex, the Daily Nation newspaper reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Malindi police chief Polycarp Etyang Wednesday confirmed that
the three suspects are being held over the killing, saying that
one of them, a recent settler in the area, is assisting the police
with information.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the murder of Calzavacca is part of a deal
related to the sale of the Oasis Village among the Italian
businessmen in Malindi.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Italian community in Malindi have volunteered
the names of several suspects in the killing, Etyang said.
</P>
<P>
As one of the suspects flew out of Kenya on Sunday morning,
police are working closely with the immigration department on the
matter, he said. 
