<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quotes of Russia's Main Presidential Candidates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian voters will go to the
polls Sunday to elect a new president among 11 candidates.
Following are some quotes of the four leading contestants.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Putin, the acting president who is widely expected to
win the race:
</P>
<P>
-- "Anyone who doesn't regret the passing of the Soviet Union
has no heart; anyone who wants it restored has no brains."
</P>
<P>
-- "The higher the degree of economic freedom of economic
entities, the higher the level of development of the state."
</P>
<P>
-- "Only one thing can be effective in such circumstances (
Chechen separatism) -- to go on the offensive. You must hit first,
and hit so hard that your opponent will not rise to his feet."
</P>
<P>
-- "These videos, their advertising (TV campaign ads by other
candidates). I will not try to find out in the course of my
election campaign which is more important, Tampax or Snickers."
</P>
<P>
-- "It is hard for me to visualize NATO as an enemy. I think
even posing the question this way will not do any good to Russia
or the world. The very question is capable of causing damage."
</P>
<P>
-- "I don't see why (Russia should) not (join NATO). I would
not rule out such a possibility, but I repeat if and when Russia's
views are taken into account as those of any equal partner."
</P>
<P>
-- "Nobody is going to admit Russia into NATO. We have never
thought this could happen."
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
Gennady Zyuganov, the Communist party leader who trails Putin
in the second place in opinion polls:
</P>
<P>
-- "Our fathers and grandfathers did not liberate Europe from
fascism for the NATO military alliance to make seven-mile steps
advancing to the east and posing a threat to Russia's national
security."
</P>
<P>
-- "The authorities are trying to conceal the truth of the
tragic situation in the country. It is my duty to bring it to each
voter."
</P>
<P>
-- "To save the country, the economic and social policy must
be immediately changed."
</P>
<P>
-- "I guarantee the recovery, within five years, of your
savings depreciated by (former prime ministers Igor) Gaidar and (
Sergei) Kiriyenko. We will restore citizens' rights to cheap
housing and communal services, to free education and health care.
The State will establish rigid control over prices for basic
foodstuffs and essentials. Electricity and communications tariffs
and transport fare will be reduced."
</P>
<P>
-- "I know where and how to find money to fulfill my program.
Our country is still very rich.
</P>
<P>
-- "I guarantee timely and fair labor remuneration, immunity
for legally obtained property. The State will support enterprises
of all forms of ownership, in town and in the country, and will
ensure equal conditions for their development."
</P>
<P>
-- "Stop the extinction of the Russian people. Ensure a worthy
future for our children and grandchildren. Restore the country's
defense potential. Provide tangible assistance to the development
of culture and enhance public spirit. Wage a resolute struggle
against crime and corruption."
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
Grigory Yavlinsky, leader of the liberal Yabloko party:
</P>
<P>
-- "The new ruling elite is neither democratic, nor Communist,
neither conservative nor liberal, neither red nor green. It is
merely selfish, greedy, and rapacious."
</P>
<P>
-- "Any action Russia takes in today's world, Russia is taking
for its own vital interests, not to please anybody or to make any
other country happy. Russia's problems should be tackled primarily
by our own selves because they are absolutely crucial for the
Russian people, for the future of Russia."
</P>
<P>
-- "Russian media remain free from direct political censorship
as before but is now controlled by the robber-barons, who, in fact,
are part of the government."
</P>
<P>
-- "In politics just as in boxing, the winner is not the one
who is stronger, but the one who's left standing at the very end."
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
Ultra-nationalist Vladimir Zhirinovsky, leader of the Liberal
Democratic Party:
</P>
<P>
-- "I advocate a military-police state with a strong army and
police structures."
</P>
<P>
--"Democracy will lead this country to an abyss. A three-
million-man army must be established and the KGB restored. This is
the only path."
</P>
<P>
-- "You have only one choice -- either me, or (acting
President Vladimir) Putin. The next president will be named
Vladimir."
</P>
<P>
-- "If bloodshed is necessary, I will shed it. And if you are
afraid, don't vote (for me)."
</P>
<P>
-- "I will spill the blood of all national-separatists,
destroy them in accordance with the Constitution, in accordance
with the criminal code. There will be KGB posts and informers
everywhere. I will know what is going on in this country. I am
telling you in advance that I will exterminate them all. Rivers of
blood will flow. Ten million or 15 million will die, but the
remaining 135 million will live normally." 
</P>
</TEXT>
