<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Star Lynch Sprains Knee Ligament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Philadelphia 76ers forward
George Lynch will be sidelined for two weeks after he sprained a
ligament in his right knee Wednesday night, the team said.
</P>
<P>
Lynch was injured less than two minutes into action. He was
battling for rebound position when Raptors center Antonio Davis
crashed into his right knee, knocking Lynch to the floor.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary diagnosis was a sprain rather than a tear and
appeared to be similar to the injury he suffered last season, when
he missed seven games.
</P>
<P>
Lynch was averaging 9.6 points and 8.0 rebounds in 66 games
this season, his second with the Sixers and seventh in the NBA. He
also is 14th in the league with 1.6 steals per game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
