<HEADLINE> Over Ten Million Farmers in Anhui No Longer Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Anhui Province in East China has
helped over ten million farmers escape poverty over the past
twenty years, a provincial official said today.
</P>
<P>
During that period, the province spent nearly 10 billion yuan (
1.2 billion U.S. dollars) on poverty-relief programs for farmers
living below the national poverty line.
</P>
<P>
These programs included construction of 10,000 schools and 100
hospitals in rural areas, in addition to roads and bridges.
</P>
<P>
The province also added 560,000 hectares of high-yield farmland,
said the official, adding that the province is redoubling its
poverty-relief efforts to help the other 780,000 poor farmers come
out of poverty by the end of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
