<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,000-Year-Old Porcelain Kiln Found in Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A porcelain kiln dating back to the
Five Dynasties (907-960) era was recently found in the city of
Huangshan in southern Anhui Province, east China.
</P>
<P>
The 1,000-square-meter kiln area was discovered at a
construction site by employees of a local enterprise. More than
200 pieces of porcelain, including bowls, dishes, kettles, and
jars have been unearthed from the site.
</P>
<P>
This discovery will provide valuable material for research into
the area's economy, culture, and folk customs, especially the
history and technology of porcelain making, in ancient time,
according to archeologists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
