<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highways to Link All of China's Counties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A highway will be built in Medog
County in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region, the only
county in China presently without access to highways.
</P>
<P>
A special team organized by the Second Surveying and Designing
Institute of the Ministry of Railways will go to the county to
choose the best route for the highway next month, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Work on the highway will be very difficult due to geological
conditions. Medog is located south of the Yarlung Zangbo River,
with many steep mountains and deep valleys, and the county is also
in a region with the highest amount of rainfall in China.
</P>
<P>
"However, we are confident of selecting the best route and
adding Medog to the national highway network," said an official
with the surveying and designing institute.
</P>
<P>
The experienced institute successfully surveyed and designed
the Nanning-Kunming Railway, also a difficult project in southwest
China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
