<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Uses Foreign Funds to Develop Forestry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
attracted more than 100 million US dollars in foreign funds to
develop its forestry since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The province has 14 foreign-funded projects, involving tree
planting, treatment of plant diseases, fire prevention and forest
industries.
</P>
<P>
A major afforestation project with 289 million yuan in
investment, including 19 million U.S. dollars in loans from the
World Bank, will fund the planting of trees over an area of 46,000
hectares, raising the forest coverage rate in the involved areas
by 5.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
At present, the province still expects foreign investment to be
used in 15 other forestry projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
