<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suzhou Strengthens Foreign Economic Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The scenic city of Suzhou in east
China's Jiangsu Province is spurring the development of a foreign-
oriented economy.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the city imported and exported 12.56
billion US dollars of goods in 1999, an all-time high, with
exports reaching 6.93 billion US dollars, up 33 percent from the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Of this figure, exports of machinery and electronic products
reached 3.81 billion US dollars, accounting for 55 percent of the
total, as the United States became the largest market for Suzhou's
exports.
</P>
<P>
The city also drew 3.57 billion US dollars of contractual
foreign investment last year.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that 8 of the world's top 500 corporations
invested in Suzhou in 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
