<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Advertising Turnover Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The business volume of professional advertising firms continued
to take the lion's share of the overall turnover, reaching 27.78
billion yuan, up 20.7 percent over 1998.
</P>
<P>
Television, newspaper, and magazine advertising turnover all
witnessed two-digit growth, hitting 15.6 billion yuan, 11.2
billion yuan, and 890 million yuan, respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, radio advertising dropped 6 percent for the first time
to reach 1.25 billion yuan last year, sources said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of l999, China had more than 64,800 advertising
units, employing some 587,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangdong Province continued to lead the
country in advertising business volume, with total turnover
accounting for more than one-third of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
China's advertising business volume exceeded 50 billion yuan in
1998, up 16.4 percent over 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
