<HEADLINE> China Opens Official Chinese IT Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- China's most influential
information technology (IT) service provider, the Center of
Computer &AMP; Microelectronics Industry Development (CCID), today
launched its Chinese IT website: www.ccidnet.com.
</P>
<P>
The new website, which used to be the site of China Infoworld,
consists of four major parts including information, business,
consultation, and public services.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the website will help CCID improve amid
the rapid changes of the new Internet era, said Li Ying, deputy
director of the center and CEO of the new website.
</P>
<P>
CCID is a government authorized organization under the Ministry
of Information Industry which offers information services on
policy-making, research, and consultation in the IT industry. It
also has the country's biggest testing organization, China
Software Testing Center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
