<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICBC Increases Fixed Asset Investment Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC), one of the country's four leading commercial
banks, plans to provide 120 billion yuan (14.56 billion U.S.
dollars) in loans for fixed asset investment projects this year.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said today that the ICBC will continue to
increase its lending to highway, power, telecommunications, and
other infrastructure projects, and inject more into hi-tech and
new industries, such as biological engineering, new energy sources,
and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC will choose a number of profitable and large
enterprises and groups to develop long-term and steady cooperative
relations, while suspending loans to loss-making, resource-
consuming, and polluting enterprises.
</P>
<P>
As for lending to small- and medium-sized enterprises, hi-tech
firms with efficient management systems will be given priority,
ICBC sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a large proportion of the bank's loans will go to
technological upgrading projects in key industries and key
enterprises, as well as those involving huge overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The bank will also extend its support to western regions for
the construction of local infrastructure and enterprise
restructuring. The proportion of its loans going to western
development projects will be increased considerably this year,
according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC also plans to enhance cooperation between its
overseas and domestic branches to provide high-quality services
for its clients worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
