<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Takes Consistent Policy on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- China has taken a consistent
policy on the Kosovo issue and has been advocating political
settlement of the issue, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun
Yuxi said here today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference this afternoon, Sun reiterated China's
stance on the Kosovo issue that the sovereignty and territorial
integrity of Yugoslavia should be respected in an earnest manner,
the legal rights and interests of all ethnic groups in the Kosovo
region should fully be guaranteed, and Resolution 1244 of the UN
Security Council should be effectively implemented.
</P>
<P>
"Only by doing so can conditions necessary be created for a
political solution of the Kosovo issue," he said, adding that
China has no self-interest in the matter, but takes principled
stance, aiming at safeguarding the UN Charter and widely
recognized norms governing international relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
