<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Publishers Focus on Western Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Since beginning of this year,
China's 32 publishing houses have published 72 books on economic
developments in western China.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that books about the large-scale development of
the west will become a hot point of China's publishing market this
year, according to today's Guangming Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Xidan Book Mansion has opened a special counter for
over 20 kinds of books on western development, and some of these
books have already sold out.
</P>
<P>
The State Press and Publication Administration and the State
Ethnic Affairs Commission have collected 10 million yuan over the
past four years to support western regions, especially those of
ethnic minorities, to develop the publishing sector.
</P>
<P>
Experts also note that there is much to be done to develop
cultural resources in western China, which will help stimulate
economic development as well as raise the scientific and cultural
awareness of the people in the west. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
