<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Benthal Imaging Equipment Developed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have developed
China's first benthal imaging equipment.
</P>
<P>
According to today's "Guangming Daily", the imaging equipment,
developed by the Acoustic Institute of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS), meets international standards.
</P>
<P>
The equipment can be used to search wrecked ships and other
substances at the bottom of the ocean, according to experts.
</P>
</TEXT>
