<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Official Calls for Continued Efforts on Family Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A senior government official has
urged to continue exercising effective control over population
growth in China, reduce the birth rate, and improve the quality of
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The issue is vital to the country's socialist modernization and
it is in the long-term interests of the Chinese nation regarding
its existence and development.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongyu, a state councilor and secretary-general of the
State Council, made the remarks at a national teleconference
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China has experienced a historic change in the reproduction of
its population as it has entered the period of low birth rate, the
state councilor said.
</P>
<P>
However, the official noted, family planning will remain a
tough task in the country as in the coming decade, its population
is expected to increase by 10 million every year.
</P>
<P>
Wang called the recent resolution on family planning made by
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the State Council a "guiding document" for the work on population
and family planning.
</P>
<P>
The work of family planning should be centered on the overall
development of human being, he said, urging that the people's
status as the master of family planning be respected and their
legal rights be protected.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
