<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stamps Featuring Chinese Calligraphy Issued in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Postal and Telecommunication
Services of China's Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR)
government on Thursday began the issuance of a set of new stamps
featuring Chinese calligraphy.
</P>
<P>
The set has four stamps with each containing a Chinese
character written in calligraphic style. Read out one by one, the
four characters means "Chinese calligraphy."
</P>
<P>
Other postal products include souvenir sheet, first-day cover
and introduction paper. A total of 750,000 sets will be issued,
with each set costing 77 patacas (9.6 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth set of stamps issued in the Macao SAR this
year.
</P>
<P>
Government sources said that one commemorative envelop will be
issued on March 28 to mark the 100th-day founding of the Macao SAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
