<HEADLINE> Kenya Warns Over British Evil Cult </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government warned that
a British cult targeting children had invaded Kenya and ordered
all institutions handling children to be alert, the East African
Standard newspaper reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Members of the notorious British cult, Children of God, have
established a base in Kenya, said Director of Children's Service
in the Ministry of Home Affairs Sammy Kwallah.
</P>
<P>
He said that two members of the cult had visited several local
children' s homes in February in search of possible recruits.
</P>
<P>
Members of the cult, which has recently changed its name to
"Family", are infamous for sexually molesting children, Kwallah
said.
</P>
<P>
He sounded an alert to all schools and children's homes to be
cautious of the cult and its followers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
