<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Observatory Opening To Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal Observatory
will be open to visitors from 9:00 am to 3:00 pm this Saturday to
mark World Meteorology Day which falls on today.
</P>
<P>
All residents with valid identification cards will be able to
enter the observatory and learn about the weather and weather
forecasting, according to today's Beijing Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
March 23 was named World Meteorology Day in 1960 to mark the
birth of the World Meteorology Organization on March 23, 1950.
</P>
</TEXT>
