<HEADLINE> Chinese Financial Website Hacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese financial website
providing investment information services was hacked on March 21
for about 40 minutes, today's China Youth Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The website: www.jrj.com.cn, was attacked by unknown hackers
during the live chat program "Analysts On-line" when participants
noticed a substantial drop in browsing speed.
</P>
<P>
An immediate investigation carried out by the website found a "
large scale" hacker attack, and normal operations soon were
resumed.
</P>
<P>
Ning Jun, CEO of the company which owns the website, said such
attacks are occurring with more frequency these days to major
websites in China.  
