<HEADLINE> China, ROK Discuss Technology Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Government officials, scientists
and technology experts from China and the Republic of Korea (ROK)
gathered at the ROK embassy in Beijing today to discuss
cooperation between the two countries in high and new technologies.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and president
of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, was among those present at
the seminar, which was organized by the ROK embassy.
</P>
<P>
Song said in his speech that with concerted efforts from both
sides, China and the ROK have made great progress in expanding
cooperation in the field of high and new technologies in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have jointly launched a number of research
institutions and nearly 100 cooperative projects in science and
technology, according to Song.
</P>
<P>
He said that the number of people involved in science and
technology exchanges is also growing.
</P>
<P>
Such increasing cooperation between the two countries will help
the development of technologies in both countries, Song noted.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China and the Republic of Korea are
neighbors and share similar cultural backgrounds. And cooperation
is mutually complementary due to the differences in resources and
stages of social and economic development of the two countries,
thus with a bright future.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and people from the scientific and
technological communities of the two countries participated in the
seminar and held in-depth discussions on technology innovation
policies, the science and technology development plans of the two
countries, and cooperation projects in the fields of
telecommunications, aerospace, nuclear energy, and high-speed
railway construction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
