<DOCNO> XIE20000323.0282 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Grain Producer Boosts Grain Production Capacity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province in northeast
China, the biggest Chinese grain producer, is expected to enjoy an
increase of 365 million kilograms in grain production capacity
this year.
</P>
<P>
The increased grain production capacity is mainly attributed to
the 224 agricultural development zones and 20 units of modern
agricultural demonstration which were newly built last year,
according to provincial officials.
</P>
<P>
As the top grain producer in the nation, Heilongjiang turned
out 3.07 billion kilograms of grain last year.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang injected a total of 800 million yuan (96 million U.
S. dollars) into agricultural development projects in 1999,
upgrading more than 173,300 ha of low-quality farming fields,
improving rural electric power grids and purchasing new farming
machinery.
</P>
<P>
Ten new high-tech agricultural parks were also initiated in the
province last year, with an aim to popularize high-yield and
better-quality strains of farm products and experiment with new
growing techniques.
</P>
<P>
In a move to further restructure its agricultural sector,
Heilongjiang has oriented its agro-projects to quality rather than
quantity, resulting in the popularization of high-quality crop,
grain and soybean and the introduction of a series of special
varieties such as European sturgeon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
