<HEADLINE> Average Ticket Price in Japan for World Cup Almost Double: Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 22 (Xinhua) -- The average ticket price for the
2002 World Cup soccer matches played in Japan will be almost twice
as much as tickets sold for the 1998 matches in France, a major
Japanese newspaper said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Japan will co-host the 2002 World Cup with South Korea. Japan
has the right to stage 32 matches, half of the total.
</P>
<P>
Quoting unidentified sources, the Yomiuri newspaper said that
the average price of about 1.5 million tickets, allotted for sale
in Japan, will be around 160 U.S. dollars per ticket.
</P>
<P>
Toshiaki Koyama, spokesman for the Japan Organizing Committee
for the 2002 World Cup, said officials are still working to set
ticket prices, which will be decided at its board of directors'
meeting on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Koyama said the cost of co-hosting the matches in Japan is
estimated at 468 million U.S. dollars. 
