<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Company Sponsors Yacht in Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A hotel in the Tibetan Autonomous
Prefecture of Hainan in Qinghai Province in northwest China signed
an agreement recently with the Hong Kong Darwick Shipping Co. Ltd.
on jointly building a luxurious yacht.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghaihu Zhangfang Hotel and the Hong Kong company will
invest a total of 4 million yuan (482,000 U.S. dollars) to build
the yacht, which is aimed to provide convenience for tourists
visiting the Qinghai Lake, China's largest inland saltwater lake.
The lake covers an area of 4,400 sq. m.
</P>
<P>
The double-deck yacht with 120 seats is expected to help
generate one million yuan (120,000 U.S. dollars) in financial
income each year. With the operation of the yacht, tourists can
enjoy sight-seeing around the lake and visit the Tibetan
Autonomous Prefecture of Haibei, where China's first atomic and
hydrogen bombs were born.
</P>
<P>
According to Li Xuansheng, an official with the provincial
tourism bureau, more and more domestic and overseas businessmen
were showing interest in investing in tourism sector in Qinghai
this year. 
</P>
