<HEADLINE> Xinhua Unveils Asia-Pacific Regional Bureau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Pacific Regional
Bureau of Xinhua News Agency was unveiled on Thursday Morning at
the news mansion at No 5, Sharp Street West, Wanchai of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the unveiling ceremony, Bureau Director Zhang
Guoliang said the Asia-Pacific region, which is adjacent to China,
maintains close ties with China in various fields, and the region
also enjoys significant international status with its rapid
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said Xinhua News Agency is China's state news agency and
has been witnessing continuous expansion in the drive to be a
worldwide press institution.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua has always attached great importance to the news
coverage in the Asia-Pacific region and set up its regional
headquarters in Hong Kong in 1984 to coordinate the news reporting
of the branches in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
To meet the demands of its development, Xinhua has officially
registered the Asia-Pacific Regional Bureau in the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR), said Zhang, who is also
director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong SAR Branch.
</P>
<P>
He noted the unveiling of the Asia-Pacific Regional Bureau,
along with the launch of the Hong Kong SAR Branch of Xinhua on
January 18 this year, shows the importance attached by Xinhua to
the Hong Kong SAR and marks a new leaf in Xinhua's undertaking in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said Xinhua has maintained fine ties with the people from
all walks of life in Hong Kong, especially with the media for a
long time, and also benefited from Hong Kong's prosperity and
stability.
</P>
<P>
As a registered press institution, he pledged, Xinhua will more
resolutely uphold the "one country, two systems" principle, more
conscientiously abide by the Basic Law and other laws of Hong Kong
SAR, and make more contribution to the implementation of the "one
country, two systems" principle and the maintenance of the
stability and prosperity of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua has now more than 100 overseas branches, including five
regional bureaus.
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Pacific Regional Bureau, the first overseas regional
bureau of Xinhua, offers news service directly to some 500
subscribers. It released 64 pieces of English news, 26 pieces of
Chinese news and 45 pieces of photo news every day on average in
1999.
</P>
<P>
Those who were present at the unveiling ceremony were Wang
Fengchao, deputy director of the Liaison Office of the Central
People's Government in the Hong Kong SAR; Tang Guoqiang, deputy
commissioner of China's Foreign Ministry in the Hong Kong SAR; and
representatives from some Hong Kong-based media. 
</P>
</TEXT>
