<HEADLINE> FIFA to Consider Granting Credentials to Online Editors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 22 (Xinhua) -- FIFA Wednesday said it was to
consider granting media credentials to journalists who publish
their reports only on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Zurich, FIFA said it would consider
creating a new category for online editors before the 2002 World
Cup in South Korea and Japan.
</P>
<P>
"In line with other major international sports organizations,
FIFA has so far refused to grant credentials to specialist online
media on the grounds of potential rights infringements and limited
space at events.
</P>
<P>
"With the Internet coming of age and being embraced on a truly
global scale, FIFA will reconsider its stance."
</P>
<P>
The media committee of the FIFA stressed that credentials would
only be considered for editors of online text services, not for
television or radio. Broadcasting rights are granted to specific
media organizations in contracted deals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
