<HEADLINE> Private Economy Booms in Coastal Fujian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The private economy has been
growing rapidly in coastal Fujian Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the number of private businesses
had reached 40,700 in the province by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of these businesses which had employed
more than 582,600 people reached nearly 20 billion yuan last year,
with a combined registered capital of 48.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The private businesses had also created an increasing number of
namebrand commodities, which helped sharpen their competitive edge
in overseas and domestic markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
