<HEADLINE> Environment Monitoring Network Built Along Huaihe River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 23 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
built up an environment monitoring network in the Huaihe River's
drainage area to control pollution and improve environment.
</P>
<P>
The central government has invested 16 million yuan in the
province to build the environment monitoring network.
</P>
<P>
With the help of the environment monitoring network, the
province will be able to launch a general pollution control
project, and prevent serious pollution accidents from happening.
</P>
<P>
Environment monitoring is one of the major environment
management measures in the province. In 1989, Anhui Province led
the country in establishing water quality monitoring stations
along the Huaihe River, which played a positive role in reducing
water pollution of the river.
</P>
<P>
The Huaihe drainage area is one of the major grain producing
areas in China, with one sixth of the country's population and
arable land.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, a large-scale pollution control program has been
launched in the area and by the end of 1997, all the polluting
enterprises along the river had met the state standards of
pollution discharge control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
