<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Probes Microsoft Purchase of British Cable Company Stake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said on
Wednesday that it has extended its anti-trust investigation into
Microsoft's planned purchase of MediaOne's stake in the British
cable company Telewest Communications.
</P>
<P>
The purchase of 29.7 percent of MediaOne's stake in Telewest
Communications would give Microsoft joint control of the cable
company with the Liberty Media Group.
</P>
<P>
European Union Competition Commissioner Mario Monti said, "We
have decided to open a full second-phase investigation and will
make a detailed assessment of the impact of the transaction on
competition conditions in various areas of the digital cable
industry."
</P>
<P>
The EU regulations allow the commission, its executive body and
anti-trust authority, four months to decide whether to clear the
deal.
</P>
<P>
The commission rarely blocks mergers or acquisitions, but
demands that competition concerns be met.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft agreed last May to buy the stake in Britain's number
two cable firm as part of a complex three-way deal.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in a statement that it had serious concerns
that the deal would strengthen Telewest's existing dominant
position as an exclusive supplier of cable services to consumers
within the area of its franchise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
