<HEADLINE> Lazio and Real Book Last Two Berths in Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 22 (Xinhua) -- Lazio broke one of the longest
unbeaten streak in modern football history to take one of the last
two berths in the quarter-finals of the European Champions League
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Serie A side beat English Chelsea 2-1 at Stamford
Bridge, where Chelsea never fell in 34 European matches stretching
back to 1958.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea went ahead just before halftime on Gustavo Poyet's 30-
meter strike, but Lazio hit the target twice in the second half
with goals from Simone Inzaghi (54) and Sinisa Mihaljovic (66).
</P>
<P>
Lazio topped the group D after the win to join seven-times
European Cup winners Real Madrid, who beat Rosenborg Trondheim 1-0
in Norway to finish second to Bayern Munich in group C, in the
last eight.
</P>
<P>
Raul scored the only goal of the game after only three minutes.
</P>
<P>
Both Lazio and Real came through with only 10 men on the field
at the final whistle. Lazio had Portuguese defender Fernando
Couto sent off six minutes from time for a second bookable offence,
while Real lost Guti who was red-carded after his second yellow
after 52 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Friday's quarter-final draw brackets group winners Barcelona,
reigning champions Manchester United, Bayern Munich and Lazio and
runners-up Porto, Valencia, Real Madrid and Chelsea.
</P>
<P>
Group winners will face runners-up and will play at home in the
second leg.
</P>
<P>
In Wednesday's other two games, Dynamo Kiev beat Bayern Munich
2-0 and Feyenoord ended with a goalless draw at Olympique
Marseille. Neither results had any affect to the final placings
of each group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
