<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two More Railways Planned to Connect Mountainous Areas of Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 12.2 billion yuan (1.47
billion U.S. dollars) will be spent to construct two new railways
connecting mountainous areas in Fujian Province in east China.
</P>
<P>
The Ganzhou-Longyan Railway line will eastwardly cut through
the mountains in southern part of neighboring Jiangxi Province and
turn south after entering Fujian, and end at Longyan in
southwestern Fujian.
</P>
<P>
The project has a total length of 282 km, of which 158 km will
be in Fujian Province. It will cost a static investment of 5.2
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Railways will be responsible for
construction and operation of the new railway, while Jiangxi and
Fujian will be in charge of land acquisition and relocation of
residents. Construction is expected to start later this year.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a feasibility study is being conducted
for the Wenzhou-Fuzhou Railway line which will stretch along the
southeast China coast from Wenzhou, China's most famous production
center of small commodities in Zhejiang Province, to Fujian
Province starting at Fuding and ending at Fuzhou, the provincial
capital of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
The new coastal railway line will have a total length of 360 km,
consisting of 263 km in Fujian and 97 km in Zhejiang. It is
estimated to cost seven billion yuan, five billion yuan of which
will be provided by Fujian and the remainder by Zhejiang.
</P>
<P>
Mountains and hills cover over 90 percent of Fujian's land,
with an area of 120,000 sq km. Building of the two new railways
will help promote local economic development and lift more poor
residents in Fujian out of poverty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
