<HEADLINE> Shandong Records Foreign Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 23 (Xinhua)-- East China's Shandong Province
reported an import and export turnover of 2.87 billion US dollars
in the first two months of this year, up 29.3 percent over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released by the provincial committee
for foreign economic and trade, the export value was 1.77 billion
US dollars, 24.6 percent higher than in the same period last year,
with the import value standing at 1.1 billion dollars, up 37.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has engaged in extensive efforts to promote its
foreign trade, especially the processing and general trade sectors,
since early this year. The province's processing industry reported
an export and import value of 1.5 billion U.S. dollars, up 33
percent over the same period of last year. The general trade
sector reported a total value of 1.2 billion dollars, up 27
percent.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, the trade with the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations account for 53 percent of the total. Other major
trade partners include the Republic of Korea, Japan, the United
States and the European Union.  
</P>
