<HEADLINE> China Supports Firms to Cut Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The facilities include those used to treat water pollution, air
pollution and solid waste and those to control noise, monitor
environmental conditions and save energy, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The circular said that manufacturers that produce these
facilities and use Chinese equipment to upgrade one of the 62
projects may withhold corporate income equal to their investment.
</P>
<P>
Taxes may also be waived for these firms that net less than 300,
000 yuan a year, said the circular. It also said the State may
also help pay for renovation or research by State-owned firms
engaged in environmental facility manufacture.
</P>
<P>
"The development of these facilities is expected to meet huge
market demands and therefore has a promising business future in
China," said the circular.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 81 percent of the State's industrial polluters meet
the State requirement. In the western areas, where environmental
protection lags behind the rest of China, 30 percent of the
industrial polluters have met the requirements, statistics form
the State Environmental Administration indicated.  
</P>
