<HEADLINE> Government Supports Pollution Cutting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- A circular issued by the State
Economic and Trade Commission this week lists 62 environmental
protection facilities in need of money or upgrades, China Daily
reported today.
</P>
<P>
These facilities are used to treat water pollution, air
pollution or solid water. Or they are used to control noise,
monitor environmental conditions or save energy.
</P>
