According to the memorandum, Sina.com will provide news and
Internet service to users of Ericsson mobile phones, and the two
sides will join hands in developing new plans for the mobile
Internet.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation between the two companies will help more mobile
phone users realize their dreams of getting on line in any places
and at any time, said Wang Zhidong, chief executive officer of
Sina.com.
</P>
<P>
China now has 40 million mobile phone users and 10 million
Internet users. Experts predicted that by the year 2003 the number
of mobile phone users in the world will reach one billion, and 60
percent of them will use mobile Internet service. By that time,
the number of mobile phone users in China will approach 200
million.
</P>
<P>
As a leading telecommunications manufacturer in the world,
Ericsson is playing an active role in promoting the use of mobile
Internet and improving the Internet infrastructure and the
compatibility between various telecommunications products, said
Michael Ricks, president of Ericsson (China) Co. Ltd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
