<HEADLINE> Lazio Advances into Champions League Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 22 (Xinhua) -- Italian soccer giant Lazio
defeated Chelsea 2-1 with a goal from Simone Inzaghi and a
spectacular free kick by Sinisa Mihajlovic to earn a place in the
quater-finals of the European Champions League Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea, already in the last eight, scored the first goal when
captain for the night Gustavo Poyet rifled a rising shot from 25
meters high into the left-hand corner of the Lazio net just before
halftime in a group D match.
</P>
<P>
But Lazio, with all to play for and dominating Chelsea in
midfield, came back nine minutes into the second half when Inzaghi
scrambled home a Pavel Nedved cross.
</P>
<P>
Mihajlovic's stunning kick from 30 meters came in the 66th
minute after a foul by Celestine Babayaro.
</P>
<P>
Lazio's Portuguese international Fernando Couto was sent off in
the 84th minute for two yellow card offences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
