Joe Cole has signed a lucrative two-year extension to his contract
which ties him to West Ham until 2004.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old midfielder has broken into the first team this
season and won his first England Under-21 cap last month.
</P>
<P>
Cole's new deal is part of West Ham's aim to keep their young
stars at Upton Park.
</P>
<P>
Michael Carrick, also 18, has also extended his contract until
2004. England stars Frank Lampard and Rio Ferdinand, both 21, are
signed up until 2006.
</P>
<P>
Company secretary Graham Mackrell said: "It's great news for
the club. We've tied up the people we want." 
