<HEADLINE> Hornets' Coleman Fined $7,500 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 22 (Xinhua) -- Charlotte Hornets forward
Derrick Coleman was fined $7,500 on Wednesday for a flagrant foul
against Toni Kukoc of the Philadelphia 76ers in Monday's game at
Charlotte Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
Coleman was assessed with a flagrant-2 foul and ejected after
he hit Kukoc in the face with 6:41 left in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
The Hornets led 36-33 when Kukoc got inside Coleman for a tip-
in. On the next possession, Kukoc beat Coleman to a rebound and
Coleman retaliated by slapping down at the ball. His hand came
across the face of Kukoc, who ended up with a scratch under his
right eye. 
</P>
