<HEADLINE> Colombia Rejects Paramilitary Proposal About Neutral Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The presidential advisor rejected the offer of the United Self
Defenses of Colombia (AUC) leader Carlos Castano, of providing a
municipality in the Bolivar department to hold there the opening
convention of dialogues with the ELN.
</P>
<P>
The paramilitary leader said Sunday that the AUC is willing to
permit the Tiquisio municipality in the department of Bolivar to
become the seat of the meeting of civilian delegates and ELN
rebels foreseen since 1998 and postponed because of the lack of an
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner for peace said that the government and the ELN
delegates "are advancing in the definition of a place and time for
the convention through confidential negotiations led by the
president, the former foreign minister and now ambassador in Cuba
Julio Londono Paredes.
</P>
<P>
The ELN and the government delegates have met at several
preparatory phases for a peace process in Havana and in Caracas.
</P>
<P>
However, the convention of delegates of the civil society that
should have been held in 1999, was postponed for an undetermined
time because of the ELN demand to demilitarize four Bolivar
municipalities, which was rejected by the government because it is
a strategic zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
