<HEADLINE> Artists Unveil Tate Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 leading UK artists
from Tracey Emin to Howard Hodgkin Thursday relaunched the Tate
Gallery as a home for British works only.
</P>
<P>
The event followed the departure of the Tate's international
collection to its new home - the Tate Modern, located beside the
Thames in London.
</P>
<P>
Tate Britain, as the old Tate building will now be named,will
hold the major collection of British artworks ranging from
Elizabethan miniaturist Nicholas Hilliard to contemporary artist
David Hockney.
</P>
<P>
Key works by van Dyck, Gainsborough and Stanley Spencer will be
on show as well as the national collection of paintings by JMW
Turner.
</P>
<P>
Six new galleries to open next spring will allow more paintings
to be brought out of the Tate's vast archive.Currently the gallery
displays just 15 percent of its collection.
</P>
<P>
The gallery's director, Stephen Deuchar, said Tate Britain will
bring a new zest to the world's largest display of art from the UK.
</P>
<P>
"We have an almost limitless capacity in the years ahead to
explore British art," he said.
</P>
<P>
A large collection of modern British art will open this summer
and the controversial Turner Prize will continue to be held there
annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
