<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose sharply
Thursday on a news report that the software maker Microsoft is
trying to finally settle its antitrust dispute with the U.S.
government.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 253.16 at 11,119.86,
recovering all its losses of 40.64 points in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 26.71 at the new record of 1,527.35 and the
technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 75.86 at 4,940.61.
</P>
<P>
The market rose after the Wall Street Journal reported that
Microsoft and the U.S. government were moving closer to settling
their dispute in the long-standing antitrust dispute.
</P>
<P>
Investors poured money both in blue chip stocks and tech shares
as the hike in interest rates was left behind their mind. The
Federal Reserve raised rates for the fifth time Tuesday in its
effort to keep inflation under control.
</P>
<P>
Shares in Microsoft and other big-name technology companies
rose, lifting the Dow index higher and leading the Nasdaq
composite's advance as well.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 9.07 at 652.31 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 6.16 at 1,036.40. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies 2.60 at 573.79.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 8-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,841 up, 1,154 down and 494
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 1.06 billion shares from 1.07 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
