<HEADLINE> Greek Left-Wing Parties Stage Protest Outside U.S. Embassy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Greek Communist
Party (KKE) and other left-wing organizations later Thursday
staged a rally and marched to the U.S. embassy in Athens to
protest the presence of NATO forces in the Yugoslav province of
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Members of KKE's youth organization burned an American flag
before the embassy, but protesters failed to hand a petition due
to the presence of a strong police force.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Greek Foreign Ministry spokesman
Panayiotis Beglitis announced Thursday that during the talks
between a delegation of senior Greek diplomats and their Turkish
counterparts, both sides agreed on the need for full
implementation of U.N. Security Council resolution 1244, respect
for the inviolability of borders and the territorial integrity of
Yugoslavia and respect for the rights of all ethnic groups living
in the province.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government has been extremely concerned over the
escalating violence in Kosovo and urged the international
community to coordinate their efforts for a quicker and viable
solution to the Kosovo problem. 
