<HEADLINE> Third Day of Israeli-Palestinian Talks "Intensive, Serious" - U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Israeli and Palestinian
delegations spent their third day of negotiations on difficult
issues concerning "the final status" in an "intensive and serious
" manner, the State Department said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The talks are continuing, intensive and serious. there's a
good atmosphere," a State Department official said.
</P>
<P>
U.S. officials will meet the two delegations separately at the
Bolling Air Force Base, southeast of Washington, later on Thursday
for an update on the progress, said the official who declined to
be identified.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Palestinian peace talks, resumed on Tuesday after
several months of suspension, were aimed at reaching a framework
agreement on their disputes concerning the final status' issues.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinians have agreed to try to reach an
agreement on the final status by September 13. But they have first
to reach a framework agreement in May so that the way toward to
the final peace between the two sides could be smoothed out.
</P>
