<HEADLINE> WTO Launches Negotiations on Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Trade Organization (WTO)
formally launched negotiations on agriculture Thursday although
members are still far apart from reaching consensus to appoint a
person to chair the Committee on Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"We still have no solution," Chairman of the General Council
Kare Bryn told reporters about the WTO hunt for a chairman
acceptable both to supporters and opponents of agricultural trade
liberalization.
</P>
<P>
According to WTO rules, the Norwegian diplomat said, he had
named New Zealand ambassador Roger Farrell, outgoing chairman of
the WTO's Council for Trade in Goods, to chair Thursday's meeting
as members believed that it was vital that the agricultural talks
should begin as planned.
</P>
<P>
Trade sources said that the initial meeting had been mainly
devoted to organizational matters like timetables and restatement
of existing views, rather than any new proposals. 
</P>
